        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 20 at 2:51AM CDT by NWS Austin/San Antonio TX</headline>
        <description>At 250 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northwest of Kerr Wildlife Management Area, or 25 miles
southeast of Junction, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hunt, Us-83 Near The Kerr-
Kimble County Line, Camp Verde, Mountain Home, I-10 Near The Kimble-
Kerr County Line, The Intersection Of I-10 And Us 290, Kerrville-
Schreiner Park, Kerrville, Ingram, Kerr Wildlife Management Area,
Waltonia, and Harper.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 500 AM CDT for south central
Texas.</instruction>
